This paper discusses the use of statistical and semantic models for extractive text summarization, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques such as TF/IDF, TextRank, and Glove Vectors, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (LG). Hence, cs.IR and cs.LG are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of pre-trained vectors and weighing techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (AI) and neural networks (NE). Therefore, cs.AI and cs.NE are also possible sub-categories.
